# No hacks or workarounds

## Requirement

- Do **not** ship temporary hacks, brittle shortcuts, or “just make it work” overlays that hide the real problem.
- Fix at the **canonical owner** of the behavior: the layer that actually defines the contract, API, or state machine.
- Preserve **governance and continuity** (doctrine, runtime lineage, numbering ownership) instead of bolting parallel paths.

## Prefer

- Identify why the bug or gap exists; change the smallest correct surface at the right layer.
- One clear code path rather than special cases that only paper over symptoms.
- If scope is unclear, **narrow the change** and document the ownership decision in the PR/commit message — do not add a second unofficial system.

## Avoid

```swift
// ❌ BAD — behavior-only shim that duplicates real policy
if isLegacyPath { return hardcodedFallback }

// ✅ GOOD — fix routing/settings/contract so the real path is correct
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — swallow errors to silence CI
catch { return null }

// ✅ GOOD — handle, log, or rethrow with a typed error at the boundary that owns I/O
```

## When blocked

If a proper fix needs design or cross-layer agreement, **stop and say so** with a short options list — do not land a workaround “for now” unless the user explicitly asks for an explicitly scoped, reversible interim with a tracked follow-up.
